The type of `group_id` is `GroupMaster` and the data type of `user.group_id` column is `INT`.  
The error says that MyBatis does not know how to convert `GroupMaster` into `INT`.

To resolve the error, you just need to change `#{group_id}` to `#{group_id.group_id}`.

```java
@Insert(&quot;INSERT INTO users(group_id, login_name, password, full_name,&quot;
        + &quot;full_name_kana, birthday, email, tel, rule, salt) VALUES&quot;
        + &quot;(#{group_id.group_id}, #{login_name},#{password}, #{full_name}, #{full_name_kana},&quot;
        + &quot;#{birthday}, #{email}, #{tel}, #{rule}, #{salt})&quot;)
```

You seem to be very new to MyBatis, so I suggest you to take some time to read the documentation.  
https://mybatis.org/mybatis-3/index.html

I also recommend using more recent version of MyBatis.  
3.4.6 supports Java 7 if you cannot upgrade to Java 8+.

